my college apartment move out vlog is now live on youtube, meaning my very last college vlog is now officially live for you to enjoy🥹

when i started college 4 years ago, i drove to tuscaloosa with $120 in my bank account & a camera in my passenger seat. since then i have been able to not just grow into a woman, but I’ve also been able to grow alongside my own online community. it truly is YOU who have made my dreams a reality and for that, I am forever grateful. 

so many “influencers” and “content creators” get a bad rep because of assumptions, allegations, & judging someone on their social media posts. I have had my fair share of hate comments & breakdowns over this don’t get me wrong, but always remembering how I started has helped me immensely. social media is not everything, but the past 4 years & endless opportunities has brought a whole new light into my life. thank you to all of those who made this possible & have been here through my whole college journey. 

while I have changed a lot the past 4 years, I have morphed into a confident woman who finally believes in herself. the past few years have been so transforming & a huge transitional period for me. closing this chapter isn’t the end, but instead it was the beautiful beginning that gave me all of you. 

so with all that being said, this girl is ready for NYC & to add some more angels to the fam, what do you say?😉

•
celebrating Elle’s health and her hard journey through FIP!💕 if you don’t know what FIP (feline infectious peritonitis) is, it is a fatal disease in cats with very harsh, painful, and expensive medication that isn’t easily accessible (and is so new, it’s still in clinical trials). we started Elle’s journey in April of this year and after 6 grueling months of injections, pills, bloodwork, and many vet visits later, she is FIP CURED!😻 we have her full journey on my youtube channel that shows clips of her injections, medication, photos, & resources. link in my bio🎥 #fipwarrior #fip #fipwarriors #fipwarriorsofinstagram #fipcured
